<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15323] read with format=text is broken for partitioned tables in Spark 2.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15323</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;sqlContext.read.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;text&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).load(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;...&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is broken for partitioned datasets in Spark 2.0&lt;br/&gt;
In the source code of the text Datasource it explicitly states that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;    Text data source doesn&apos;t support partitioning.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/commit/bc3760d405cc8c3ffcd957b188afa8b7e3b1f824#diff-de9933c0e2fa74747b33ab62ebc6af8eR94&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/commit/bc3760d405cc8c3ffcd957b188afa8b7e3b1f824#diff-de9933c0e2fa74747b33ab62ebc6af8eR94&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is problematic for me since I&apos;ve code relying on this functionality which works without any problem on Spark 1.6.1&lt;/p&gt;

